CFC Bank of Kenya Climbs Most in Month Before Dividend Payment

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-05-19T10:39:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/cfc-bank-of-kenya-climbs-most-in-month-before-dividend-payment.html
CFC Stanbic Holdings Ltd. (CFCB) , the Kenyan
unit of Standard Bank Group Ltd., rose the most in more than a
month on the last day shareholders can buy its shares to be
entitled to receive a dividend.  The stock rallied 4 shillings, or 7.1 percent, to 60
shillings at 1:19 p.m. in Nairobi, the capital, the biggest jump
since April 14.  The company announced a final dividend of 0.804 shilling a
share on March 21, according to a report on the website of the
 Nairobi Stock Exchange . The dividend will be paid on May 25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
